Introducing: The Little Artist Collection 👩🏼‍🎨 

Calling all aspiring artists! Bring your child’s art to life on tote bags, sweaters and stationery. 

I am always inspired by the wild imaginations of my boys. They love to show off their drawings and paintings to classmates, friends and family, but when days get busy those drawings often disappear — crumpled at the bottom of a backpack or hidden away in a drawer… Cue the inspiration behind the Little Artists Collection! Now, you can feature your child’s favorite drawings on their very own tote bag, stationery set or sweater. Our family has loved doing this for years, and I couldn’t wait any longer to share it with you all! 

Check out our website for a simple step-by-step tutorial on how to upload your child’s work. We can’t wait to see what your kids come up with! 

xx, LouLou

Behind the scenes with my little artists! With only so much space on the fridge, our latest collection is the perfect way to display and preserve your children’s favorite drawings and artwork. Wow, there are 20,000 of you here! Thank you 💙🤍 Since there are so many new faces I thought it might be a good time to re-introduce myself 👋🏻
 
My name is LouLou Baker, and I really stumbled into this wonderful, whimsical, watercolor world (woah!) by accident. After graduating from art school, I initially worked in fashion and photography. It wasn’t until I designed a deck of playing cards for the island my family spends the summer on that I realized people would be interested in purchasing my work. Ten years later, I haven’t stopped! I’m the mom of two amazing little boys who inspire so much of my work — lots of trucks, Safari animals and comfy pajamas in my house!
 
I am so happy that you’re here and so grateful that you all support me as I continue to do what I love. The opportunity to share some of life’s most special moments — from baby showers to bachelorette weekends to weddings — is not lost on me. Xx, LouLou
